<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-10T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="1039" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1039">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">853.00 Revolution 1931/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Funchal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Huddleston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Funchal</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-10T16:00:00-01:00">April 10, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 10—3:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I regret if plan has caused Department embarrassment. Will relieve
                            Department and Minister Lisbon of any and all responsibility and will
                            make full apologies in accordance with any instructions to be received
                            from Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Huddleston</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>